Values for final 7 variables.

Values for final 7 variables. All units are in Gg Carbon Var1A = Annual Change in stock of HWP in use form consumption Var1B = Annual Change in stock of HWP in SWDS from consumption Var2A = Annual Change in stock of HWP in use produced from domestic harvest Var2B = Annual Change in stock of HWP in SWDS produced from domestic harvest Var3 = Annual Imports of wood, paper products, wood fuel, pulp, recovered paper, roundwood/chips Var4 = Annual Exports of wood, paper products, wood fuel, pulp, recovered paper, roundwood/chips Var5 = Annual Domestic Harvest Var6 = Annual release of carbon to the atmosphere from HWP consumption (from fuelwood & products in use and products in SWDS) Var 7 = Annual release of carbon to the atmosphere from HWP (including fuelwood) where wood came from domestic harvest (from products in use and products in SWDS)

finalVariables(Years = 1990:2015, Variable = paste("Var", c("1A", "1B",
  "2A", "2B", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7"), sep = ""),
  decaydistribution = c("Exponential", "K=2"), halflives = halfLives)

Arguments

Years
years to calculate
Variable
variable to return
decaydistribution
decay distribution to use (if necessary)
halflives
half-lives for calculation (if necessary)

Value

a numeric vector of values for the selected variable for `Years`

Examples

finalVariables(Variable = 'Var1A')
#>  [1] 17107.1033 13423.0348 15742.9581 16753.3412 18320.6135 17204.3066
#>  [7] 17344.7304 18935.3265 19077.9747 21281.0645 19920.3191 16605.7670

#> [19]  2342.2767 -5606.6893 -2418.5332 -1823.2435  -677.4553  2194.7400
#> [25] 11061.9029 13896.0643
